Agreed. Some people still use 4.02.0; we should hunt them, understand their
use-case (I heard it could be something so simple to fix that "this PR I
use the automatic opam switch for was submitted for 4.02.0"), and move them
to 4.02.1.

Please speak up if you're concerned! There is no good reason to suffer the
atrocious compilation times.

